tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant hyperglycemia with normal HbA1c, suggesting possible acute glucose elevation. Lipid profile is markedly abnormal with high total cholesterol, high LDL, high triglycerides, and low HDL, indicating increased cardiovascular risk. Renal function and electrolytes are within normal limits, and there is no evidence of microalbuminuria. Recommend further evaluation and management of dyslipidemia and hyperglycemia.
